sentences: Schröter was born in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, January 16, 1960.
Schröter began his career in 1975 performing piano recitals at age 15 in Brazil.
He graduated with a degree in music in 1988.
Best Interpretation of Villa-Lobos, Brasilia/DF - Brazil - 1976 (16 years old)
Winner of the orchestra soloist competition - OSPA/Porto Alegre/RS, 1985
Semifinals in Internacional Piano Competition in Montevideo - Uruguay, 1985
Prize in Chopin national competition in Curitiba/PR - Brazil, 1986
Canzonneta for wind quintet op.163 and Nocturne for piano no.12 Selected by Oregon Literary Review, 2006.
In 1993–1994 he traveled to Germany Master Class with Ceslaw Kacinsky, Jorg Demus, and Peter Rosel
In 2000–2001 he traveled to the U.S. to perform in recitals
When he was just nine years old, Wilhelm started to accompany his aunt Maria Schroeter, a soprano, on piano performing pieces by Franz Schubert and Robert Schumann.
Schröter no longer tours and now concentrates on composing.
Schröter received his first award at 16 years of age.
Best Interpretation of Villa-Lobos, Brasilia/DF - Brazil - 1976 (16 years old)
